<TITLE> Two Shibir men held in Rangpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangpur, Apr 22 (bdnews24.com)  Police arrested two activists of Islami Chatra Shibir, the student wing of the Jamaat-e-Islami, on Thursday in Rangpur district town on charges of planning "large scale" subversive activities. Rashidul Islam, a sub-inspector of Rangpur Sadar police station, told bdnews24.com that police arrested Abdul Bari, a first year honours student of Begum Rokeya University, and Mahfuzur Rahman of Phulbari upazila in Kurigram at around 1 pm when "some ICS activists were having a secret meeting" at a house behind Rangpur circuit house. "They were preparing for large-scale destructive activities," he said. Islam said police arrested the two while the others managed to flee jumping over the wall. He said a large number of Jihadi books and CDs were seized from different rooms of the house. Mohammad Shafi, the owner of the house, said some youths had rented it 20 days back. Abdur Rashid, the officer in-charge of Rangpur Sadar police station, told bdnews24.com that the detained were being questioned. bdnews24
